{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, reliance on cheap, low-quality foods has continued to drive food insecurity and diet disparities, which have increased socioeconomic and health disparities among poor populations (Darmon & Drewnowski, 2008).",
    "Market and advertising theory show that marketing strategies influence consumer decisions on food delivery sites.",
    "Through persuasive advertising and user engagement strategies, users are encouraged to order unhealthy food online and avoid healthy eating habits.",
    "Food delivery software analyzes users' preferences through big data and constantly pushes content and ingredients matching their tastes (Li et al., 2024).",
    "For example, once a user orders a hamburger, the platform continues to push fast food content, making it harder for users to resist unhealthy eating temptations."
  ]
}